values:
I'm so numb it's disgusting.
We both know what we need to do, but neither one of us want to face it. 
When it comes down to it, nobody wants to face reality; we just want to go on pretending like everything is okay. 
Nobody wants to hurt, to be sad and lonely. Even if it means happiness in the end. But the end is far and the present is here. The present is what will keep us in a rut until we finally see the bigger picture. Ignorance is bliss. 

I should write for Grey's Anatomy.

Well here I am in Wisconsin. Sad to be away from friends but nice to see family.

I pretty much already had christmas. My beautiful boyfriend bought me a ring! (Not an engagment ring or anything!) That was my favorite present. And maybe the fake ID my mom found for me since the bastards at Peabody's took mine. Other than that Christmas was good.

Now Im stuck up here for 10 days probably ending up to be bored out of my mind. I'll get  some good shopping done. And I'm soooo excited to eat at my favorite restraunt Maggianos!! YUMM!

New Years will probably be one of the worst since everyone is going to Vegas. Oh well. Least I will be home for it spending it with close friends.

Well I'm going to try and go to bed. Tomorrow we're food shopping and hopefully finding a gym=]

ps. I'm watchin James and the Giant Peach! I love this movie!!

I am a rich lady. Well not really but since I have never made money before, it's amazing! I don't mind working either. Keeps my summer from being boring. AND I made new friends!

So everyone come and visit me at TGI Fridays!!!!!

<3

I used to never care, now i cant stop.

actions speak louder than words.
all I hear is volume. Your volume.
It pierces the ackward silences 
yet is paralyized by reality.

I know what I know,

But without motions

not now, not ever, especially not today.

I used to never care, now I cant stop.

Golly Golly. I start college soon. I will have to be a big girl on many levels. Im excited!

I am so content with life at the moment. I don't think I've had things so figured out. I got wonderful friends, a perfect boyfriend, and a supporting family. I even got a brand new car!

23 days left and any stress I have will be gone.

=D

I don't think her smile could have gotten any bigger.


=D

Im slowly breaking down the wall I have built up inside,
Im realizing I do have friends. Good ones. Lots of em!

Im happy.

Beat that.

tomorrow will be worse.

I make everything into a plan.
I am a planner.
I like to multi-task too.

I sometimes wish I wasn't a planner. 
But at least that means I am dependable.
That also opens up a new subject.
Is a day a week worth it?

You broke my heart in your hurtful ways. 
That I just hope you can pick up the pieces and put it back together before it's too late.

Imissyou.

Dear Grandma, 
I hope your in heaven. And Im happy you are no longer suffering. Im sorry the last couple years I havn't really been close like we used to be. Blame it all on me. I just wanted you to know that everything you did was perfect. I'll miss so much about you, you don't even know. I'll miss your laugh, your smile, your swimming "froggy style", your cooking, your advise, your purfume that we always tried so hard to find, but most of all I'll miss how every night you told me you loved me no matter what I did. And would kiss my forehead and you gave that little giggle. I miss that so much. I hope you are dancing with the angles, and I look forward seeing you again when I die. I always imagined you at my wedding so when that time comes, please be there too. I love you so much Grandma, Watch over me. 

Love your oldest granddaughter,
Lindsey

Here you stand seething with guilt.
Silence only justifies this act of cowardice.
The look stapled on your face cries out for forgiveness,
the one thing that I cannot give.

(Did you ever see that one person
and the way they do these things
and it hurts you so much it's like choking choking choking
down the embers)

I can give you freedom from your guilt,
with a flick of my wrist onto yours.
I can give you peace of mind with a forced smile.
I can give you death with the look upon my face.

This is your freedom in a life of fallacy,
with no last kiss and no regrets;
you don't deserve good bye.
This is your freedom in a life of fallacy,
with no last kiss and no good bye.

Here you stand seething with guilt.
Silence only justifies this act of cowardice.

With a short story, the one you add to daily, you are the tragic loss.
No story book ending for this fairy tale of you.
Just the one composed with blood taken from your pen that you hold in your
lifeless hand.
Cry for you. Shed tears. Mourn. Wish the end.
Cry for you. Shed tears. Mourn. Wish the end.

(Did you ever look, did you ever see that one person,
and the subtle way that they do these things and it hurts so much?
So much like choking down the embers of a great blaze.
It's that moment when your eyes seem to spread aspersions
and to scream confessions at the insipid sky parting clouds.
You let this one person come down in the most perfect moment.
And it breaks my heart to know the only reason you are here now is
A reminder of what I'll never have
I'll never have... I'll never...
Standing so close knowing that it kills me to breathe you in.
Standing so close knowing that it kills me to breathe you in.
But this table for one has become bearable.
I now take comfort in this, and for this, I cherish you.
Did you ever look, did you ever see that one person
and the subtle way that they do these things and it hurts so much?
So much like choking down the embers of a great blaze.
It's that moment when your eyes seem to spread aspersions
and to scream confessions at the insipid sky parting clouds.
And you let this one person come down, come down.
I cherish you...I cherish you.
Just say you would do the same for me.
Just say you would do the same for me.
Say you would do the same...
Just say you would do the same for me.
For as much as I love Autumn,
I'm giving myself to Ashes.)
